<TEXT>
the mother of aslain utah tourist testified 
monday that civilians not police came to the familys rescue 
while her son lay fatally stabbed in a manhattan subway station 
the family of mugging victim brian watkins returned to new york 
from provo utah for the first time since the sept 2 murder to 
testify before the us senate transportation appropriations 
subcommittee which is exploring ways to pay for improved subway 
safety 
karen watkins her voice strong and unwavering recalled what 
happened after a gang of muggers attacked the family and stabbed 
her son brian 22 
i had asked the token booth clerk to call 911 he just ignored 
me so i ran outside there were two pay phones out there that were 
being used at the time by two gentlemen and i asked them to call 
911 
a man told her there was another phone on the train platform he 
ran downstairs with her jumped the turnstile and opened an exit 
door so she could bypass the turnstile and get onto the platform to 
call 911 
mrs watkins said the token booth clerk never said a word to 
me at all my son was lying not more than 5 feet from him but he 
did not respond 
the transit authority has disputed this account saying the 
clerk used an emergency phone in his booth to summon police and 
paramedics 
brians brother todd testified that it took about 10 minutes 
for official help to arrive after the 911 call 
watkins a former high school tennis star was on an annual trip 
to the us open tennis tournament with his brother mother father 
and sisterinlaw 
they were attacked at a station in midtown manhattan at around 
1030 pm 
a group of youths set upon watkins father sherwin slashing 
his pants with a knife and stealing a money clip containing about 
200 in cash and some credit cards brian and todd interceded when 
mrs watkins was punched in the face 
brian was stabbed in the chest he collapsed while chasing the 
suspects and died 40 minutes later at a hospital 
i dont think there was anything that really alerted us to 
the imminent danger mrs watkins said 
maybe looking back we should have been a little more careful 
as we watched these young boys run into the subway and not pay the 
toll we just thought they didnt want to pay the fare and were 
running to catch the train 
eight suspects have been charged with seconddegree murder in 
watkins killing 
todd watkins read a statement on the familys behalf that said 
the death of brian watkins has shocked the city of new york it 
has made new yorkers realize that there is no safe place in the 
city and that crime is rampant 
the oneday hearing was held by sen alfonse damato rny 
and sen frank r lautenberg dnj 
zenia mucha a spokeswoman for damato said the senators 
office invited the watkinses to testify she said an airline 
donated airfare and a hotel donated accommodations 
</TEXT>
