<DOCNO> AP900917-0002 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
scores of children are hurt each year by lawn 
darts despite a ban on the dangerous toys that have killed and 
maimed a study found 
i want people across the country to simply throw these things 
way said dr sara sotiropoulos who led researchers at the 
childrens mercy hospital in kansas city mo 
even though the sale of these has been banned there are 
supposedly 10 million sets of these in garages across the 
country ms sotiropoulos said monday in a telephone interview 
lawn darts were designed for use outside in a game played like 
horseshoes they have heavy pointed tips 
theyre just too dangerous said ms sotiropoulos now 
practicing pediatrics in bellingham wash 
in the study published in the september issue of the american 
journal of diseases of children ms sotiropoulos and colleagues 
examined data on 76 children injured by the darts from 1973 to 
1988 
three of those children were killed by the darts and more than 
half suffered serious head injuries such as skull fractures and 
brain lesions she said 
congress and the consumer product safety commission banned lawn 
darts in the fall of 1988 until the ban lawn dart injuries were 
responsible for an estimated 675 emergency room visits a year 
according to the cpsc 
in 1989 after the ban an estimated 439 such visits were blamed 
on the darts department statistics show 
the study examined data on children aged 19 months to 18 years 
including 69 cases reported by the cpsc of those 49 percent were 
hospitalized and 13 percent suffered lasting damage such as 
blindness or brain damage 
the six additional children studied all suffered serious head 
injuries they included a 7yearold boy injured when a thrown dart 
pierced his cheek and entered his brain ms sotiropoulos said 
the boy who was admitted to the kansas city hospital 
contracted meningitis because of the injury and remains in a coma 
nearly two years after he was injured she said 
pediatricians should educate parents about this hazard and 
encourage them to discard all lawn darts the study said 
the darts were manufactured by several companies which are 
prohibited from making the devices under the 1988 ban said cpsc 
spokesman ken giles 
 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

