<TEXT>
a computer entrepreneur described by a 
judge as a master manipulator was sentenced monday to life in 
prison for persuading his teenage daughter to kill his wife 
david arnold brown 38 displayed no emotion as superior court 
judge donald a mccartin told the affluent businessman his sentence 
left no possibility of parole 
prosecutors convinced jurors that brown plotted his wifes death 
so he could marry his teenage sisterinlaw who he later tried to 
kill 
the circumstances of this case are unbelievable mccartin 
said you are a scary person for you to be able to get one of 
your children to kill your wife you make charlie manson look 
like a piker 
in a separate matter monday brown was given a sixyear prison 
term for a jailhouse plot to kill his current wife another man and 
jeoffrey robinson the lead prosecutor in his case the sentence is 
to run concurrently with the life sentence 
youre just a master manipulator mccartin said i dont 
know how you could do that to another human being 
defense attorney gary pohlson said the sentences were exactly 
what i expected 
brown owner of a computer company was convicted in june of 
masterminding his wife lindas death and persuading his then 
14yearold daughter cinnamon to commit the slaying 
cinnamon brown spent three years in a youth prison before she 
told authorities that her father planned the murder and urged her 
to carry it out on march 19 1985 
while the girl was jailed brown collected 835000 in life 
insurance taken out on his wife and married patricia bailey the 
younger sister of the slain woman 
ms bailey a minor at the time her sister was killed pleaded 
guilty to participating in the scheme and was imprisoned by the 
california youth authority in may 1989 
</TEXT>
