<TEXT>
angered by iraqi raids on the french and 
other diplomatic compounds in kuwait un representatives say 
theyre considering extending to air corridors the international 
embargo on trade with iraq 
on sunday the security council unanimously passed a resolution 
condemning iraq for violating diplomatic territory with fridays 
raids and warning that further sanctions were likely if baghdad 
continued to ignore un resolutions 
the us ambassador thomas r pickering said another 
resolution would be drafted to impose an air embargo a step the 
united nations has never taken against a nation 
an air blockade would involve the interception of planes 
approaching iraq and would pose a far greater danger of triggering 
hostilities than the boarding ships in the persian gulf which has 
been done under the un naval embargo 
by singling out diplomatic missions for attack iraq confirms 
its preference for instruments of force to instruments of diplomacy 
and negotiation pickering said 
western diplomats say sanctions are also planned against nations 
that break the embargo the un imposed on trade with iraq after 
saddam husseins forces invaded kuwait on aug 2 
the ambassadors of the security councils five permanent members 
the united states britain france china and the soviet union 
met at the french mission on sunday to begin laying the groundwork 
for further resolutions 
pickering and other diplomats said they expected a vote by the 
end of the week 
if iraq persists there will be other resolutions soviet 
ambassador yuliy vorontsov said the cumulative effect will 
produce the necessary result a political solution a solution 
without any kind of military activity 
president francois mittrrand of france said saturday that his 
country wants the united nations to widen the embargo on iraq to 
include air traffic and punishment of countries or companies 
violating the sanctions 
the swift move on the air embargo indicated how seriously the 
western world views iraqs storming of the french belgian dutch 
and canadian compounds the detention of diplomats and seizing of 
three frenchmen 
iraq attacked the resolution as part of a vicious hostile 
campaign led by the united states and its allies 
iraq categorically rejects that it had kidnapped foreigners 
from former diplomatic premises or is holding them as hostages a 
foreign ministry spokesman said in a report by the iraqi news 
agency 
work on the new resolutions began hours after the council in an 
emergency session sought by france voted 150 early sunday to 
condemn iraq for its storming of embassy compounds 
the resolution was the seventh adopted overwhelmingly by the 
council to deal with the crisis sparked by iraqs lightning 
invasion and annexation of the oilrich emirate 
the four embassies raided were among some 17 that have remained 
open in kuwait in defiance of an iraqi order to close iraq cut 
utilities to many embassies and surrounded missions with troops to 
force diplomats to leave 
the iraqi government considers kuwait a province of iraq and 
says the 1961 vienna conventions on diplomatic and consular 
relations do not apply those treaties set forth the inviolability 
of diplomatic compounds 
in its latest resolution the council said it strongly 
condemns aggressive acts perpetrated by iraq against diplomatic 
premises and personnel in kuwait as well as the abduction of 
foreign nationals who were present in those premises 
it demanded the immediate release of all foreign nationals 
although iraq has allowed western women and children to leave 
many men have been sent to strategic sites to serve as shields 
against potential attack by usled forces 
an air embargo would require cooperation from iraqs neighbors 
they would have to close their air space to iraqbound flights 
refuse refueling to planes headed for iraq and report suspicious 
flights to the security councils sanctions committee 
state department officials say privately that the few flights 
now going into baghdad are not considered a threat to the integrity 
of the embargo and that it would be impossible for iraq to 
effectively break the sanctions with airlifts 
 
