since iraq invaded and occupied kuwait on 
aug 2 the security council has passed seven resolutions 
condemning baghdad and ordering action intended to force the iraqis 
into withdrawing 
aug 3 the security council votes 140 to condemn the invasion 
and demand the immediate and unconditional withdrawal of iraqi 
troops yemen the only arab member of the council abstains 
aug 6 the council votes 130 to order an embargo on trade with 
iraq and occupied kuwait cuba and yemen abstain 
aug 9 the council votes 150 to declare iraqs annexation of 
kuwait null and void in international law 
aug 18 the council votes 150 to demand that iraq free all 
detained foreigners 
aug 25 the council votes 130 to give the united states and 
other naval powers the right to enforce the economic embargo by 
halting shipping to those countries cuba and yemen abstain 
