the yen fell against the us and european currencies as 
investors sold the japanese currency in an attempt to correct 
overbought yen positions said toru kanai a currency analyst with 
new japan securities co 
institutional investors had bought the yen and sold 
substantial amounts of european and us currencies before settling 
their accounts for the first half of fiscal 1990 he said the 
middle of the standard japanese fiscal year comes at the end of 
september 
today such investors bought the dollar at about 1364013650 
yen to make up their short or oversold positions kanai said 
weakness in the bond and the stock market also contributed to 
the yens weakness he said 
