the presidentially appointed advisory body to the endowment have 
urged that frohnmayer eliminate his antiobscenity pledge which 
has stirred widespread protests in the arts community 
the senate committee also is expected to suggest that the pledge 
be dropped when it issues its formal report on the bill which 
would extend the neas life for five years beyond sept 30 when 
its statutory authority expires 
also expiring that day will be a ban on nea support for works 
that may be considered obscene specifically including 
depictions of homoeroticism sadomasochism and the sexual 
exploitation of children 
