after a 10day sail across the ocean the system 
that once was hurricane isidore reached the cold waters of the 
north atlantic and lost its tropical characteristics forecasters 
said monday 
isidore which formed sept 7 was downgraded from a hurricane 
early sunday it continued to weaken monday and was expected to be 
absorbed by a north atlantic storm by tuesday said forecasters at 
the national hurricane center in suburban coral gables 
isidore remained no threat to land hurricane specialist miles 
lawrence said 
at noon edt isidores center was near 515 degrees north 
latitude and 370 west longitude or about 625 miles southeast of 
the southern tip of greenland 
the system was heading northeast at 25 to 30 mph with winds of 
45 mph 
isidore was the ninth named storm of the 1990 atlantic hurricane 
season which ends nov 30 weather systems are named after when 
their sustained winds reach 39 mph 
tropical storms become hurricanes when their top winds reach 74 
mph 
