a consumer group on monday demanded that ford 
motor co recall 240000 ranger pickup trucks and bronco ii utility 
vehicles to fix gear shift levers that in some cases have broken 
off in the drivers hand 
fords offer of free repair of any broken shift lever if the 
truck is still under warranty is woefully inadequate said 
samuel cole vehicle safety staffer for the center for auto safety 
ford has designed a defect into these vehicles for which it 
must now take proper action and conduct a recall cole said 
with such a high failure rate it will only be a matter of time 
before we begin seeing accidents attributed to the gear shift 
defect 
ford spokeswoman joy stinson said the company did not consider 
the problem a safety hazard even if the lever breaks the vehicle 
remains in gear and the driver is able to pull off the road without 
losing control she said 
whatever gear it breaks in its driveable she said for 
that reason a safety recall is not warranted 
the national highway traffic safety administration launched an 
investigation of the gear lever problem last june 
ford provided the agency with a september 1988 internal report 
that disclosed 6473 gear shift lever failures on 1986 and 1987 
ranger pickups with manual transmissions made by mazda 
that translates into a failure rate of one in every 37 vehicles 
the center for auto safety said 
the bronco ii has the same transmission as the ranger ms 
stinson said 
ford began using an improved lever assembly with 1988 models 
the company informed the government july 16 it would provide an 
extended warranty service program in which owners would receive 
free repairs 
but the offer covered only trucks whose levers had actually 
broken and that were still covered by the companys sixyear 
60000mile warranty 
the center for auto safety in a letter to the government 
agency said the company should do more an inability to shift 
gears can result in loss of vehicle control and endanger lives it 
said 
we believe a defect is a defect and ford ought to own up 
to it and recall the vehicles cole said 
the center a private consumer advocacy organization founded by 
ralph nader urged the national highway traffic safety 
administration to order a recall of the ford trucks and investigate 
gear lever failures on mazda vehicles using the same transmission 
