for us its not a weekend hike or a walk every five years for 
us its an everyday lifestyle 
ms marr was among about 200 loggers mill workers and community 
leaders from oregon and washington state who sought out members of 
congress to plead that they keep the plight of timber workers in 
mind when considering legislation that would reduce timber cutting 
legislation that would ban logging on 63 million acres 
including about 27 million acres currently open to timber harvests 
is expected to be considered by the house interior committee later 
this week 
the push to protect northwest forests intensified this summer 
when the spotted owl was declared protected under the endangered 
species act scientists say the only way to ensure the owls 
survival is to restricting logging 
a federal task force has been trying to work out ways to protect 
the owl but still minimize the economic impact on timber workers 
rep denny smith rore said white house chief of staff john 
sununu has told him that there is little liklihood that 
environmental and economic considerations could be balanced in the 
spotted owl deliberations without congress changing the endangered 
species act 
