controversy that raged at last months pga championship 
racial policies became an issue in golf after news reports that 
shoal creek country club near birmingham ala site of the pga 
championship had no black members 
townsend said his membership in the augusta club site of the 
annual masters tournament came up five or six weeks earlier in a 
meeting in washington 
i had a meeting there with members of augusta national which 
was prompted by the chairman of our company john curley who 
mentioned my name to some folks he said 
it was around the same time as shoal creek but they made it 
clear that it accepting a black had been discussed months 
before said townsend its conceivable that the shoal creek 
thing put in on the front burner but it was not a direct result of 
that 
</TEXT>
