rock hill and environmentalists inc of columbia said the order 
would shield broad classes of information from being released from 
the facility and would reduce public access 
the environmental groups are challenging approval of a permit 
for thermalkems existing incinerator by south carolinas 
department of health and environmental control 
ron stanley appointed to hear an administrative appeal of 
thermalkems permit is considering the order which would prohibit 
the groups from discussing what they learn from subpoenaed 
documents obtained as part of the hearing it also would restrict 
the groups from discussing what they see during a tour of the 
companys hazardous waste incinerator in southwestern rock hill 
stanley had ordered thermalkem to schedule the plant visit by 
