paul lewis the united nations correspondent for 
the new york times has been named the first recipient of the 
kornferry international journalism award for excellence in united 
nations reporting 
the award recognizes the american journalist who contributes 
most significantly to the understanding of the united nations 
the award was established last year by kornferry international 
a leading executive search firm in cooperation with the business 
council for the united nations the council comprised of nearly 
100 corporations was founded more than 30 years ago to provide a 
better understanding of the united nations throughout the business 
community 
lewis will be honored at the bcun ambassadors dinner on sept 18 
in new york where he will receive the firstplace prize of 5000 
the runnersup were ethan schwartz of the washington post josh 
friedman of new york newsday and moses schonfeld of fairchild 
broadcast news 
