as their greatgrandparents and grandparents did when they built a 
whiteframed mosque known as the mother mosque in 1934 
the original mosque was like a family club says taha a 
eltawil the imam or spiritual leader of the center people 
came there with their children and family it was like a community 
gathering place 
the mother mosque was the center of activity for the citys 
muslims until 1972 when the islamic center opened to accommodate a 
growing population the center built for about 500000 has five 
classrooms a small library a large lecture hall offices and the 
traditional prayer hall where the faithful bow on a thick dark 
blue carpet as they face northeast to pray 
it still is a gathering place once a month theres a family 
picnic once a year theres a picnic for the community eltawil 
says 
