portauprince haiti ap relentless poverty in haiti has 
driven an estimated 7000 to 8000 children into the streets of 
this capital city they survive as beggars thieves and 
prostitutes 
the heads of families cant provide for themselves much less 
their children so the children are on the street says jean 
robert chery a social psychologist 
chery runs a training center for 150 boys for the montrealbased 
canadian center for research and international studies the boys 
range in age from 6 to 20 and nearly all are homeless 
chery and his four coworkers feed the boys give them medical 
care and try to prepare them for school and jobs the boys learn to 
read and they play dice and board games to improve their math 
but first chery says they must learn the most basic of skills 
how to wash up in the morning how to sit up straight how to 
talk to somebody 
fifteen of the boys are practicing homosexuals and 
threefourths have had homosexual relations some for money and 
some because of sexual confusion chery says 
its precocious sexuality the psychologist says they 
live in promiscuous conditions they have no mother or father they 
have no one to identify with sexually 
the younger boys suffer from malnutrition their hair turns 
yellow and theyre very very skinny chery says many of the 
older boys are infected with venereal diseases although so far 
there have been no detected cases of aids 
they come here and tell their life stories and i find out 
theyre criminals chery says they should be in probation 
