some tissue iacono says 
the us ban on federal funding for research on fetal tissue 
transplants was imposed in may 1988 the following november a 
national institutes of health advisory committee concluded it is 
morally acceptable to use human fetal tissue from legal abortions 
for research and therapy 
but that recommendation was rejected last november by health and 
human services secretary louis w sullivan he extended the ban 
indefinitely saying such research will increase the incidence of 
