burt reynolds says it was his own vision of 
how he would like to live if he wasnt an actor that brought about 
creation of the cbs sitcom evening shade 
reynolds had been living in florida with his wife actress loni 
anderson and their son quinton and was looking for a comedy 
about a family in a small southern town that brought him to linda 
bloodworththomason of designing women 
linda wanted to do something about arkansas because shes from 
a little town in arkansas reynolds says i wanted to do comedy 
with somebody special when the word got out that i wanted to do 
halfhour comedy a lot of people responded i talked to a lot of 
people but the projects didnt excite me as much as hers because 
hers was about a family in a small southern town which is exactly 
the way id like to raise my son because i grew up that way 
she asked me what id be if i couldnt be an actor i said a 
teacher or a high school football coach thats the way the 
character evolved 
reynolds best known for hit movies such as smokey and the 
bandit hooper and the cannonball run plays wood newton 
a former pro football player who returns to his hometown in 
arkansas with his wife and three children to coach the high school 
football team 
marilu henner plays his wife charles durning is his best friend 
and ossie davis is the philosophical owner of a barbecue stand and 
the shows narrator it also stars hal holbrook as his 
fatherinlaw and elizabeth ashley as an eccentric aunt 
woods a very familyoriented man who has a wonderful sense of 
humor about himself reynolds said during a rehearsal break at 
cbsmtm studios he loves small town values his teams not 
winning because he doesnt have any material and in arkansas 
winning is very important in football hes not real happy about 
that but he has three wonderful kids and his wife is about to have 
another one 
bloodworththomason also suggested that reynolds try his hand at 
a script 
ive done a lot of rewriting he says id like to very 
much the blank piece of paper just scares me i admire people who 
can sit down and stare at it and do something 
in florida reynolds had starred for two years in the abc 
mystery movie bl stryker 
the show worked but it was the wrong night he says we 
were in the top 20 until abc moved us from monday to saturday the 
decision to move it to saturday was suicide when they did that i 
hit the ground running i started telling people im ready to do a 
halfhour comedy 
for 16 years reynolds concentrated on making movies before 
returning to television his first tv appearance was in 
riverboat in 1959 he was in gunsmoke and later starred in 
hawk and dan august 
after deliverance in 1972 made him a bankable movie star he 
became a boxoffice champion with such hits as the longest 
yard smokey and the bandit semitough hooper and 
the cannonball run but his last hit was best little 
whorehouse in texas in 1982 and his movies slumped at the box 
office after that 
part of the slump can be attributed to rumors that he had aids 
which made it difficult for him to get cast in good movies 
actually he had injured his jaw doing a stunt and it developed 
into temporomandibular joint disorder it caused an inner ear 
problem that affected his balance and it made eating so difficult 
he lost a lot of weight 
for two years i couldnt get a job he says i weighed 145 
pounds i had to take five physicals to get a job i had to take 
the pictures that were offered me i did action pictures because i 
was trying to prove that i was well i did pictures like malone 
heat and rent a cop 
ive never been so brutalized by reviewers i got criticized 
and beat up like crazy they said i was washed up my career was 
over i went to television because i had to ill be back ill be 
back on my terms 
reynolds says he has no fear of taking roles that cast him as an 
older man he played a 65yearold safecracker in breaking in 
i dont care as long as the parts are good whether i play 
somebodys father or grandfather its a question of whether youre 
working if youre working it doesnt matter 
