<TEXT>
les miserables makes more than just money 
the longrunning musical hit helps build careers 
since it first opened on broadway in 1987 the show has given 
nearly a dozen mostly unknown performers a chance to play the 
leading role of jean valjean 
in new york and around the country 10 actors have portrayed the 
heroic valjean starting with colm wilkinson who originated the 
role in london in 1985 wilkinson was followed by country singer 
gary morris the bestknown among the valjean replacements the 
rest in subsequent tours and extended stays in cities like san 
francisco have not been household names 
the part is currently being played on broadway by craig 
schulman and he assumed the role in the classic show business 
style schulman went from the chorus of the musicals first touring 
company to eventually starring in the broadway edition of the show 
the performer first encountered les miserables in october 
1987 when he was hired as an understudy and as a member of the 
ensemble of the first national company he was in the chorus for 
only three months when he took over the lead on tour last january 
schulman graduated to the broadway production 
and the show has led to more offers to sing opera another of 
schulmans amibitions 
les miserables is an opera as far as im concerned 
schulman said the other day in the star dressing room backstage at 
the broadway theater im not doing anything different from what 
ive been training and aspiring to do although i get to show off 
my acting skills more in this show 
so what does he call himelf an opera singer who does musical 
theater or a musical theater performer who does opera hes not 
sure but is happy performing in both worlds 
casting people and producers really do want to pigeonhole you 
into a particular type or a particular category schulman says 
i had four months off last fall to sing hoffmann in the tales of 
hoffmann at virginia opera and the production was very very 
successful 
schulman always wanted to be a performer although he didnt 
know where he was headed 
schulmans first theater job when he hit new york from long 
island in september 1979 was with the light opera of manhattan a 
small troupe specializing in gilbert and sullivan the pay was low 
the conditions primitive but the experience invaluable when 
schulman left two years later he had done some 650 performances 
it was wonderful training he recalls it was the kind of 
place where you realize after a time that if you can work there 
under these conditions you can work anywhere for anyone and 
survive 
schulman left for a tour of the merry widow 
youve heard of busandtruck tours he says this was 
just a bus and we played everything from high school gymnasiums to 
real theaters working with a minimum of scenery and whatever 
lighting was available it was 55 cities in 10 weeks 
he did meet his future wife monica on the tour they were 
married in 1983 and now have two sons 
i decided that operetta was a lot of fun but knew that i 
wasnt going to make a fulltime living at it he says and i 
didnt see myself as a songanddance man for shows like chorus 
line or 42nd street 
he settled down to study opera while working at a temp job and 
an occasional opera role with small companies 
i did my first la boheme for 250 for two weeks of rehearsal 
and three performances he says i also learned a lot about 
supply and demand in this business the producers wound up bringing 
in a harp player who was paid 500 
schulman also auditioned for training programs in opera 
becoming an apprentice at the chautauqua opera near jamestown ny 
he felt he needed the extra training because at age 27 he was 
getting into opera later than most people 
in june 1987 he auditioned for les miserables which had 
opened on broadway four months earlier 
he got the job in the touring company but was undecided 
particularly since he had an offer to sing in manon in 
virginia 
i took a chance on les miserables he says i knew that 
eventually there would be a busandtruck tour and i knew there 
was going to be a los angeles company and i knew that eventually 
they would need replacements for the broadway company 
he was on the road for nearly two years leaving the tour in 
early september 1989 with the guarantee he would open on broadway 
the following january he has been there ever since 
the hardest part about this role is maintaining discipline 
about living my life for the next performance its a very 
difficult role because of my training and my background it 
doesnt hurt me to do it but i need to get a lot of rest and not do 
a lot of anything else 
