luster through the years for people who like to do it themselves 
through the years paint oxidizes as its exposed to air waxes 
and acrylic clearcoat finishes protect the paint from 
oxidation which can dull the color 
nonabrasive waxes are best for new or relatively new finishes 
especially clearcoat ones they help clean surfaces and bring 
out the shine in a finish 
if a wax with abrasives is used on a new clearcoat finish 
