to environmental regulations 
it also says participating car washes change the mixtures of its 
soaps and additives to match the time of year more bug lifters in 
the summer and more salt dissolvers in the winter 
everyone agrees that the most important time to wash a car is 
right after rain or snow storms when it may have picked up 
sulfuric acids and road salts that can damage its finish 
