operations in last years first quarter general mills gained 77 
million from discontinued operations 
general mills chairman bruce atwater told shareholders at the 
companys annual meeting that he wants sales to triple by the year 
2000 to more than 19 billion a year last years sales were 64 
billion 
separately the companys board of directors approved a 
twoforone stock split effective oct 10 
