probe 
the conduct of these traders is regulated to ensure that their 
customers from around the world are treated honestly assistant 
us attorney tom durkin said in opening arguments before you is 
a group of people who decided to play by their own rules 
the trial follows the indictment of a clerk and 18 soybean 
traders after a 1988 fbi investigation that also covered the 
chicago mercantile exchange the clerk and other eight traders have 
pleaded guilty 
at least five defendants who have admitted guilt are scheduled 
