conversations in the trading pit while posing as a trader durkin 
said in court 
they were confident they wouldnt get caught durkin told 
the jury before us district judge george marovich they broke 
the rules to make money that they are not honestly entitled to 
prosecutors used large placards to explain to the jury where the 
alleged crimes occurred visual aids also were used to describe how 
soybean futures are traded 
the soybean traders are among 48 people indicted last fall at 
the worlds two largest futures exchanges twenty avoided trial by 
pleading guilty and one by pleading no contest 
