<TEXT>
trans world northwest and united joined other 
major airlines monday in imposing an additional 42 percent fare 
increase that will raise domestic tickets by a total of 972 
percent since iraq invaded kuwait 
the higher rates go into effect on oct 1 as airlines try to 
recoup some of the extra money spent on jet fuel which has risen 
by about 50 percent since the aug 2 invasion 
last month airlines boosted domestic fares by 53 percent to 
partially offset the higher fuel costs 
the latest round of increases bring the industrys major players 
to the same levels of higher fares 
twa spokesman jim faulkner said airlines will not be able to 
recover all of the costs they have absorbed recently as passengers 
have used up old cheaper tickets while flying on planes that used 
the more expensive jet fuel 
airlines were unsure whether they will be catching up with the 
higher costs once the higher rates go into effect 
thats beyond our speculative abilities because it requires 
seeing into the brain of saddam hussein and we dont have that 
capability northwest spokesman bob gibbons said 
the second wave of fare increases was begun by pan am which 
announced a 44 percent increase on top of its earlier increase 
airlines that responded last week with announcements of 
additional 42 percent fare increases included american america 
west usair delta and eastern 
